# PROJECT OVERVIEW
Windows-native WPF desktop FEA app. Wraps CalculiX (ccx.exe) + Gmsh (Python API) for
3D linear-static structural analysis. Workflow: import STEP → mesh → assign BCs/loads →
solve → visualize (stress/displacement heatmaps + deformed mesh).
Scope: 3D linear static solids only (C3D4/C3D10 tets). SI units throughout (m, Pa, N, N·m);
UI displays mm/MPa/GPa via conversion.
Stack: WPF/.NET 8 (C#) + HelixToolkit.Wpf 3.1.2 + Python 3.11+ (gmsh, numpy) + CalculiX.
Full canonical spec: `claude.mb` (repo root). This file (`progress.mb`) is the live
task/state tracker; `claude.mb` is the architecture source of truth.

# ARCHITECTURE
Three projects + Python scripts + tests:
- src/FEASolver.App (WinExe, net8.0-windows, WPF/MVVM via CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)
  - ViewModels: MainViewModel (workflow state machine), ViewportViewModel (HelixToolkit
    3D scene, face hit-testing, BC/load glyphs), PropertiesViewModel (BC/load assignment),
    ResultsViewModel (colormap, deformed mesh, principal-stress calc), ModelTreeViewModel,
    ConfigDialogViewModel.
  - Services: PipelineService (orchestrates Mesh→ResolveNodes→WriteINP→ccx→ParseFRD),
    MeshingService (subprocess mesh_step.py), SolverService (subprocess ccx.exe),
    ResultService (subprocess parse_frd.py), ConfigService (appsettings.json), MeshCacheService.
  - Views: ViewportView, ResultsView, PropertiesView, ModelTreeView, ConfigDialog.
- src/FEASolver.Core (net8.0, shared models + pure services — referenced by App and Tests)
  - Models: MeshData/Node/Element/FaceGroup, BoundaryCondition, Load (+LocalizedLoadData,
    DirectionMode, LoadType), MaterialModel, ResultModels (ResultField/ResultSet), MeshExtensions.
  - Services: ExportService (CSV), ToolValidator, VerificationService, PhysicsVerificationService,
    ModelDiagnostics, IConfigService, IMeshCache.
  - Numerics: PrincipalStress (symmetric-3x3 eigenvalues; added 2026-06-14 to fix audit-001).
- src/FEASolver.Scripts (Python, called via subprocess; file-based JSON IPC)
  - mesh_step.py: STEP→Gmsh→mesh.msh + mesh_data.json. write_inp.py: FEAModel JSON→.inp.
    parse_frd.py: .frd→results.json. verify_solver.py / verify_physics.py / verify_synthetic.py.
  - utils/: gmsh_utils.py (face mapping, TET10→C3D10 midside swap 8<->9, consistent lumping),
    inp_writer.py (InpWriterV2 typed + legacy InpWriter; torque_to_nodal_forces r²-weighted),
    frd_reader.py (fixed-width FRD float parser), models.py (dataclasses), mesh_io.py, mesh_cache.py.
- tests/FEASolver.Tests (xUnit, references Core) + tests/scripts_tests (pytest).

DATA FLOW: STEP → mesh_step.py → mesh_data.json → MeshData (C#) → user assigns BC/Load on
faces → FEAModel JSON → write_inp.py → model.inp → ccx → model.frd → parse_frd.py →
results.json → ResultSet (C#) → HelixToolkit colormap.

KEY CONVENTIONS: 1-based node/elem IDs (CalculiX). HelixToolkit Y-up vs CalculiX Z-up.
Face IDs = Gmsh physical surface tags. CalculiX tet face order S1..S4 = corner idx
[0,1,2],[0,1,3],[1,2,3],[0,2,3]. C3D10 consistent surface lumping: corners 0, midsides A/3.
Torque distributed as r²-weighted nodal force couple: F_i=(T/D)(a×r_perp_i), D=Σ|r_perp|².

# CODING PRINCIPLES
- SI internally; convert at UI boundary only. Explicit units (no bbox-heuristic unit guessing).
- File-based IPC + subprocess; no shell=True (Python), UseShellExecute=false (C#); explicit exe paths.
- Tests-first for fixes; numerical code validated against analytical/reference (numpy) values.
- Minimal, atomic, root-cause fixes; one branch + PR per audit item (fable/fix/<desc>/<id>).
- No secrets in code. Path-traversal/extension guards on user file inputs.
- Audit artifacts + JSON live in docs/audit/ with date prefixes.

