# TASKS
## Completed
- Full repo audit → audit_summary.json + 1-page md (docs/audit/2026-06-14_*).
- audit-002 (HIGH): C# test suite never compiled/ran. Fixed: added `using Xunit;` to
  ExportServiceTests.cs + Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk PackageReference. 27 tests now run.
- audit-001 (HIGH): principal-stress eigenvalues wrong for shear/repeated roots. Fixed:
  new FEASolver.Core.Numerics.PrincipalStress (validated vs numpy); ResultsViewModel
  delegates to it. +10 PrincipalStressTests. Suite 27→37 green.
- progress.mb initialized (this file).
- Torque glyph investigation (user-reported "linear, wrong direction"):
  * FINDING: glyph geometry (ViewportViewModel.AddTorqueGlyph) was ALREADY a correct
    300° right-hand torus arc — proven via SVD of the generated point cloud (2 large
    in-plane extents, 1 tiny out-of-plane = tube). "Linear" was a stale build and/or a
    too-thin tube (~0.5% of diagonal). Hardened: bigger arc, ~2.4x thicker tube, 48×14
    segments, bigger arrowhead. (commit 55bff51)
  * REAL BUG FOUND + FIXED: PropertiesViewModel.ComputeFaceNormal (FaceNormal torque-axis
    mode) used arbitrary winding of the first 3 face node IDs → normal sign not guaranteed
    outward → torque axis (and glyph) reversed ~50% of the time. This fed the SOLVER
    (Localized.AxisDirection → torque_to_nodal_forces), so it was a physics-direction bug.
    Fixed: orient outward via away-from-tet-4th-vertex rule (same as INP writer), averaged
    over element-faces; centroid fallback. Verified on a reference tet. (commit 25ff946)

- audit-003 (MED): _strain_vonmises wrong coeff (1/3 → 2/9). Fixed in frd_reader.py;
